Description: Part of a wooden comb, about two-thirds of the original object, one side missing. Fine teeth, some broken off. The surfaces of the handle are decorated with a large central drilled circular depression, surrounded by lighter incised circles.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: University of Colorado Museum
Curator's comments: See William Y Adams, The West Bank Survey from Faras to Gemai. Sudan Archaeological Research Society Publication Number 13. BAR International Series 1335 (2005).
Acquisition name: Donated by: University of Colorado Museum
Additional IDs: Miscellaneous number: 18634 (University of Colorado Museum number)
